explanation: The solution uses a 2D array to keep track of the available seats. The gather function iterates over the rows and checks if there are enough consecutive seats available. The scatter function also iterates over the rows and checks if there are enough consecutive seats available, and if so, marks them as unavailable. The time complexity is O(k) because in the worst case, we need to check k seats. The space complexity is O(n*m) because we need to store the availability of seats for each row.

